36
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,010
It should complement its aroma.

37
00:02:25,010 --> 00:02:25,850
Alright.

38
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:26,920
As for the rest of the fish,

39
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,360
we'll do trial dishes for a few days.

40
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:29,850
Recommend it more to our guests.

41
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:30,680
Okay.

42
00:02:32,060 --> 00:02:32,900
Liu Yan,

43
00:02:33,130 --> 00:02:34,340
you should also use this chance

44
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:35,980
to train on the consistency
of serving this dish.

45
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:37,020
Got it, Mr. He.

46
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:44,100
If you have confidence

47
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:44,940
in your abilities,

48
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:46,850
start showing me from now.

49
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:48,090
I will.

50
00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:51,810
Mr. He,

51
00:02:54,690 --> 00:02:56,620
why let some newcomers

52
00:02:56,620 --> 00:02:57,850
teach us how to cook?

53
00:03:02,010 --> 00:03:03,500
Are you really asking me,

54
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:05,660
or just venting your feelings?

55
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:09,660
I've been at Highland for eight years.

56
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:12,290
If this keeps going like this,

57
00:03:13,410 --> 00:03:15,290
I don't see a reason to stay.

58
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:16,250
Kanta,

59
00:03:17,380 --> 00:03:19,180
I think you're just letting off steam.

60
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:22,940
Mr. He...

61
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:47,460
I'll help you out.

62
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:49,620
Thanks.

63
00:03:51,410 --> 00:03:52,250
Be careful.

64
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:14,220
Whoa, what brings you here?

65
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,410
Why start a fight right away?

66
00:04:17,410 --> 00:04:19,460
That's how a boxer shows gratitude

67
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:20,700
and shares happiness.

68
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:23,930
Is it done?

69
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:28,520
So, about that...

70
00:04:28,530 --> 00:04:29,610
Mr. Bai, who sells

71
00:04:29,610 --> 00:04:31,130
dried bamboo shoots,
how did you convince him?

72
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:35,340
Should we start the timer?

73
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,140
Fine, let's start timing.

74
00:04:45,530 --> 00:04:46,900
So how did you convince Mr. Bai?

75
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,020
You were so sure back then.

76
00:04:50,370 --> 00:04:51,260
Don't be fooled by Mr. Bai.

77
00:04:51,290 --> 00:04:53,290
He always acts super tough.

78
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:55,290
Actually, the one who calls the shots

79
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:56,930
is that old lady.

80
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:59,290
She loves

81
00:04:59,290 --> 00:05:00,460
the dishes you make.

82
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:03,260
So Mr. Bai does what she says.

83
00:05:03,610 --> 00:05:04,450
That's it.

84
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:13,780
You're making this up, right?

85
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,140
You know,

86
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:17,700
your biggest skill is

87
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,170
lying with a straight face.

88
00:05:19,170 --> 00:05:20,290
So how did he finally agree?

89
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:21,700
Just tell me, okay?

90
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:23,170
I want to know the story

91
00:05:23,170 --> 00:05:24,900
behind this dish.

92
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:25,980
Come on. It's not for free.

93
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:27,290
I'm even timing myself here.

94
00:05:29,850 --> 00:05:31,850
And now you're stomping? Really?

95
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:35,700
Well...

96
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,850
I...

97
00:05:37,850 --> 00:05:39,170
Then...

98
00:05:40,020 --> 00:05:41,260
No, don't do that.

99
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,100
Is it really that serious?

100
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:42,950
Just let it go.

101
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,050
Come on, let it be.

102
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:47,300
Please, have a seat.

103
00:05:47,370 --> 00:05:48,210
Alright.

104
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:51,460
That's what happened.

105
00:05:51,460 --> 00:05:52,930
He had an apprentice

106
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:53,970
who suffered

107
00:05:53,970 --> 00:05:56,020
a work injury there.

108
00:05:56,020 --> 00:05:57,780
Then, I helped that apprentice

109
00:05:57,780 --> 00:05:59,260
sue him.

110
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:01,020
He paid some compensation.

111
00:06:01,020 --> 00:06:02,820
That's why Mr. Bai
holds a grudge toward me.

112
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:07,850
Then, why would he agree to help us?

113
00:06:07,850 --> 00:06:08,820
Could it be a trap

114
00:06:09,290 --> 00:06:10,850
for revenge?

115
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:12,050
It's really not that serious.

116
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:13,780
Because his employment contract

117
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:15,140
had issues.

118
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:16,050
Originally,

119
00:06:16,050 --> 00:06:17,850
I could've asked him

120
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:19,530
for double or even triple
the compensation payment.

121
00:06:19,530 --> 00:06:20,460
But I didn't do that.

122
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:22,320
If I did,
it'd be like taking advantage, right?

123
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,370
This time I explained

124
00:06:23,370 --> 00:06:24,410
everything to him.

125
00:06:24,410 --> 00:06:25,530
At the same time,

126
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,900
I helped him revise
a new employment contract

127
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:30,220
for free.

128
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:31,610
So that's why he...

129
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:37,260
That's like a thief

130
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:39,370
inventing an anti-theft lock, right?

131
00:06:43,530 --> 00:06:47,260
Timer on.

132
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:49,260
End it.

133
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:52,050
I'm honestly so tired.

134
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:53,850
I've been way too busy lately.

135
00:06:53,850 --> 00:06:55,900
I have so much to do every day.

136
00:06:56,460 --> 00:06:57,610
Next time, before you come,

137
00:06:57,610 --> 00:06:58,610
could you maybe

138
00:06:58,610 --> 00:07:00,460
send me a message to check first?

139
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:02,050
Just show a little respect for my job,

140
00:07:02,050 --> 00:07:02,890
okay?

141
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:04,100
Okay?

142
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:10,660
Lu Tianchi,

143
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:12,530
you're honestly acting

144
00:07:12,530 --> 00:07:13,700
really strange today.

145
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,100
When I came, I saw

146
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,530
some sketchy people hanging around.

147
00:07:16,780 --> 00:07:18,020
They looked like gamblers.

148
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:19,170
Seriously, I'm not...

149
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:20,010
Don't let me find out

150
00:07:20,010 --> 00:07:21,380
that you're mixed up
with those gamblers.

151
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:22,610
Or we can't be friends anymore.

152
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:24,860
Wait a second!

153
00:07:26,020 --> 00:07:26,860
What is it?

154
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:31,580
How much time is left

155
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:32,930
on our employment contract?

156
00:07:34,140 --> 00:07:35,100
I'll tell you when it's done.

157
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:36,020
I won't come back.

158
00:07:57,690 --> 00:07:58,580
Excuse me.

159
00:07:58,580 --> 00:07:59,780
Line up!

160
00:07:59,970 --> 00:08:01,460
I'm going to my own place.

161
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:02,780
Get in line!

162
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:04,530
Are you serious?

163
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:07,290
Eating my food?

164
00:08:07,530 --> 00:08:08,460
Drinking my drinks?

165
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:10,100
Go away!

166
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:10,940
Go!

167
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:12,460
Go away!

168
00:08:23,030 --> 00:08:24,370
- Power's out.
- What's going on?

169
00:08:24,490 --> 00:08:25,330
What's happening?

170
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:26,780
The power's out.

171
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,130
Why is there no power?

172
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:30,130
Everyone, quiet down.

173
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:31,770
It'll be back soon, just relax.

174
00:08:31,770 --> 00:08:32,850
Next, please. Next one.

175
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,890
My name's Bob Marley.

176
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:39,060
Yeah.

177
00:08:39,370 --> 00:08:40,210
It's me.

178
00:08:41,650 --> 00:08:44,030
The company
that tricked you is called...

179
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:44,890
Putai.

180
00:08:45,970 --> 00:08:46,810
Putai...

181
00:08:48,590 --> 00:08:50,250
Putai, Putai.

182
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:52,370
- I...
- Putai.

183
00:08:52,370 --> 00:08:53,900
Okay, I see. So when did you

184
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:55,090
get scammed?

185
00:08:55,090 --> 00:08:56,420
Back in 1993.

186
00:08:56,770 --> 00:08:59,130
When did you start betting?

187
00:08:59,130 --> 00:09:00,230
I was just 19.

188
00:09:00,230 --> 00:09:02,020
Started at 19, betting on...?

189
00:09:02,030 --> 00:09:03,100
The League Cup.

190
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:04,650
Scored four in one match.

191
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,370
Two assists.

192
00:09:08,730 --> 00:09:09,650
Hit the post twice.

193
00:09:11,180 --> 00:09:13,540
Ronaldo was 19.

194
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:19,060
So how much did you lose?

195
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:20,460
10...

196
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:21,300
100,000?

197
00:09:21,420 --> 00:09:22,260
Yeah, 100,000.

198
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:24,010
Started with 100,000.

199
00:09:24,010 --> 00:09:25,920
Chased it to 500,000, got 150,000 back.

200
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:27,660
I thought that sounded good.

201
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:29,160
I wanted it all back.

202
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,930
That was just the start.

203
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:45,010
Then they said add more...

204
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:46,580
The total, all in!

205
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:48,010
So, how much in the end?

206
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:50,700
960,000.

207
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,490
You could borrow that much?

208
00:09:52,490 --> 00:09:55,300
10% of 960,000 is...

209
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:56,850
That's 96,000.

210
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:57,690
Right, 96,000.

211
00:09:58,250 --> 00:09:59,940
96,000. Listen,

212
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:01,500
finding Mr. Lu,

213
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,860
you've come to the right person.

214
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:04,940
Mr. Lu is famous for being fair

215
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:06,180
and just.

216
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:08,060
You'll get everything back.

217
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,460
I know a lot of people like that.

218
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:10,420
Hundreds of them.

219
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:11,340
I know them all.

220
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:12,740
Yeah, I have your contact info.

221
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:14,100
I can tell you're the type

222
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:15,780
who can turn things around.

223
00:10:15,780 --> 00:10:18,660
So I'll get part as commission, right?

224
00:10:19,380 --> 00:10:20,500
Alright, that's enough.

225
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,860
- That's enough.
- Sis.

226
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,110
Wait, listen to me.

227
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:23,980
Mr. Bob, about that...

228
00:10:23,980 --> 00:10:24,860
Next one!

229
00:10:25,540 --> 00:10:26,620
There are too many people.

230
00:10:26,620 --> 00:10:28,380
- Alright.
- Next, please.

231
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:29,940
Can you not discuss commission

232
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:30,980
with my people here?

233
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:32,900
Then, while you're here,

234
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,340
could you keep your voice down?

235
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,420
If Liu Yan finds out you're here,

236
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:37,000
- she could tear my house down.
- Relax.

237
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,020
Once I get the money,

238
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:39,740
I'll disappear right away.

239
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:40,820
Without a trace.

240
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:42,540
Next...

241
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,140
One.

242
00:10:44,820 --> 00:10:48,100
(Lu Tianchi Legal Advice)

243
00:10:54,340 --> 00:10:55,380
Look at you.

244
00:10:55,820 --> 00:10:58,340
Seriously, look who you bring home.

245
00:10:58,340 --> 00:11:00,900
Don't mess with those mole people.

246
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:01,740
Okay?

247
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:04,020
You'll end up on the losing side.

248
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:05,140
A whole group ate

249
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:06,700
so much of my stuff.

250
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,620
Does this cash

251
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:09,220
even cover the cost?

252
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:24,860
Wang Daxiang, you dare come back?

253
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:26,540
What were you thinking?

254
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:29,340
You ran off when things blew up.

255
00:11:30,780 --> 00:11:31,980
The repainting costs

256
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:33,660
come from my wages.

257
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:36,060
I didn't run away, why would I?

258
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:37,980
My mom's sick, so I have to
care for her at the hospital.

259
00:11:37,980 --> 00:11:39,340
You've got the nerve
to mention your mom?

260
00:11:40,060 --> 00:11:41,100
You're out there gambling,

261
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,100
leaving her alone

262
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,220
in the hospital.

263
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:44,780
Do you even have a conscience?

264
00:11:46,050 --> 00:11:48,140
I heard you've started
creating new dishes.

265
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:49,980
All this has proved your ability.

266
00:11:50,220 --> 00:11:51,740
Neither of us really lost anything.

267
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,900
How is that no loss?

268
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,700
Wang Daxiang, you actually came back.

269
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,700
Does the manager know?

270
00:11:58,140 --> 00:11:59,380
Does Mr. He know?

271
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,540
Forget them.

272
00:12:00,540 --> 00:12:01,860
I could tear you apart myself.

273
00:12:02,980 --> 00:12:04,780
I have my own way of coming back.

274
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:06,420
I never asked for your help.

275
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:15,340
Wang Daxiang,
did I help you for nothing?

276
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:20,420
Of course, I owe you big time.

277
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:22,140
As for the money I owe you,

278
00:12:22,540 --> 00:12:24,020
I'll return it with interest.

279
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,140
Besides, this restaurant's huge.

280
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,650
How could I set it off
with just a cigarette?

281
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,620
Where were the hotel staff?

282
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:33,620
And sprinklers? Cameras?

283
00:12:33,660 --> 00:12:34,860
I took the blame for the higher-ups.

284
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,700
Secretly, maybe they're grateful.

285
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:39,500
Where did you get the money?

286
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,500
It's my salary, just got paid.

287
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:43,860
Thanks for visiting my mom.

288
00:12:44,860 --> 00:12:45,700
You're a good person.

289
